[30;1m785 | [0m[35m    The implementation also provides confidence intervals[0m
[30;1m786 | [0m[35m    for each prediction using a bootstrap of little bags approach described in [rf3]_:[0m
[30;1m787 | [0m[35m    subsampling is performed at hierarchical level by first drawing a set of half-samples[0m
[30;1m788 | [0m[35m    at random and then sub-sampling from each half-sample to build a forest[0m
[30;1m789 | [0m[35m    of forests. All the trees are used for the point prediction and the distribution[0m
[30;1m790 | [0m[35m    of predictions returned by each of the sub-forests is used to calculate the standard error[0m
[30;1m791 | [0m[35m    of the point prediction.[0m

[30;1m596 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m224 | [0m[35m          `int(max_features * n_features)` features are considered at each[0m
[30;1m225 | [0m[35m          split.[0m
[30;1m226 | [0m[35m        - If "auto", then `max_features=n_features`.[0m
[30;1m227 | [0m[35m        - If "sqrt", then `max_features=sqrt(n_features)`.[0m

[30;1m296 | [0m[35m        # Estimate final model of theta(X) by minimizing the square loss:[0m
[30;1m297 | [0m[35m        # (prel_theta(X) + (Y_res - prel_theta(X) * T_res) * Z_res / cov[T,Z | X] - theta(X))^2[0m
[30;1m298 | [0m[35m        # We clip the covariance so that it is bounded away from zero, so as to reduce variance[0m
[30;1m299 | [0m[35m        # at the expense of some small bias. For points with very small covariance we revert[0m
[30;1m300 | [0m[35m        # to the model-based preliminary estimate and do not add the correction term.[0m
[30;1m301 | [0m[35m        cov_sign = np.sign(cov)[0m
[30;1m302 | [0m[35m        cov_sign[cov_sign == 0] = 1[0m
